<HEADLINE>
CENTRAL NEWS AGENCY'S 2007 WORLD ALMANAC AVAILABLE
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan.  24 (CNA) 01/24/07  19:44:11 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
The 2007 World Almanac compiled by the Central News Agency has
been on sale in domestic bookstores since early January.
</P>
<P>
The latest edition contains several news features, including the
current situation of 25 royal households around the globe, the
world's top 500 businesses, as well as a global competitiveness
ranking.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-language almanac also features a historical chronicle
of Taiwan covering 460 years as well as a photo collection of
unforgettable moments in Taiwan during the last year.
</P>
<P>
The book also contains in-depth analyses of the hottest issues in
Taiwan and around the world by experts and CNA correspondents
stationed abroad.
</P>
<P>
The Who's Who section of the almanac lists the names and
backgrounds of around 2,000 public figures in Taiwan. Well-known
model Lin Chih-ling, Taiwan-born Yankee pitcher Wang Chien-min,
and Cloud Gate Dance Theater Founder Lin Hwai-min are among the
latest entries.
</P>
<P>
The first section includes pieces on major news events and the
latest trends in the world, as well as the 10 people with the
most potential in their respective fields in Taiwan, the top ten
domestic news and top ten international news stories of 2006, and
a chronicle of the Republic of China in 2006 and of the world
over the last 100 years.
</P>
<P>
The second section includes a brief introduction to Taiwan's
geography and people, Taiwan's government organizations and
leaders, as well as historical sites in Taiwan and Fujian, the
results of the Taipei  and Kaohsiung  mayoral and councilor
elections,  the "mega-investment"  and "mega-warmth"  projects
launched  by the Executive Yuan, and much more.
</P>
<P>
The third section covers international  affairs,  including in-
depth analyses of the latest international situation and an
introduction to the 200 countries around the world, while the
final section deals with cross-Taiwan Strait relations over the
past year.
</P>
<P>
The yearbook also comes with a DVD that features Notes of News
compiled by CNA, as well as name lists of leading international
organizations,  Nobel Prize winners,  domestic universities and
colleges, and much more.
</P>
<P>
The 2007 World Almanac, priced at NT$550, is available at
domestic bookstores or for purchase directly from CNA.
</P>
